"{\"uid\": \"dw.com-en-france-holds-bastille-day-festivities-before-paris-olympics-a-69655355\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"France remembers the storming of the Bastille prison in 1789 every year on July 14, a key event in the French revolution.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 121, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 6, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9989634872975586, \"rank\": 0.0010260130694498633, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 37, \"end\": 45, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Storming_of_the_Bastille\", \"score\": 0.9999964138078852, \"rank\": 3.586091267637556e-06, \"text\": \"Bastille\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Storming_of_the_Bastille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Storming_of_the_Bastille\"}, {\"begin\": 103, \"end\": 120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Revolution\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French revolution\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Revolution\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_Revolution\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This year's celebrations come after a turbulent snap election and ahead of the Paris Olympics.\", \"from\": 122, \"to\": 216, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Francecelebrates its national holiday, Bastille Day, on Sunday as the country prepares to host theOlympic Games.\", \"from\": 218, \"to\": 330, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"President Emmanuel Macron opened the traditional military parade by reviewing the troops, followed by the Marseillaise, the national anthem.\", \"from\": 331, \"to\": 471, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 341, \"end\": 356, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Emmanuel Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Preparations for the\\u00a0Games have blocked the military parade from its traditional route on the Champs Elysees, forcing a military contingent to march on the nearby Avenue Foch instead.\", \"from\": 473, \"to\": 656, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 567, \"end\": 581, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"score\": 0.9918285953524741, \"rank\": 0.008238720428601937, \"text\": \"Champs Elysees\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Due to Olympic security measures, the number of troops were reduced compared to previous years.\", \"from\": 658, \"to\": 753, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some 4,000 people, down from 6,500 last year, and 162 horses marched in the tightly choreographed show.\", \"from\": 754, \"to\": 857, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"No tanks or armored vehicles took part, but overhead more than 60 aircraft flew\\u00a0in formation, including a British Typhoon fighter alongside French Mirages and Rafales.\", \"from\": 858, \"to\": 1025, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 964, \"end\": 971, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9992733804638462, \"rank\": 0.0006749782319525232, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 998, \"end\": 1004, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.505261373725146, \"rank\": 0.7963014140834302, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This year's parade did not feature a foreign guest like last year'svisit by Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi, but it did have a very special participant: the Olympic flame.\", \"from\": 1027, \"to\": 1202, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1103, \"end\": 1124, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_India\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Indian Prime Minister\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Prime_Minister_of_India\"}, {\"begin\": 1125, \"end\": 1138, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Narendra_Modi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Narendra Modi\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Narendra_Modi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Narendra_Modi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Just 12 days before the start of the Summer Games, the torch relay reached the French capital.\", \"from\": 1203, \"to\": 1297, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1282, \"end\": 1288, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.505261373725146, \"rank\": 0.7963014140834302, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Colonel Thibault Vallette, of the elite Cadre Noir de Saumur cavalry school and Rio 2016 equestrian gold medalist, carried\\u00a0the torch.\", \"from\": 1299, \"to\": 1432, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1339, \"end\": 1349, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cadre_Noir\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cadre Noir\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cadre_Noir\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cadre_Noir\"}, {\"begin\": 1353, \"end\": 1359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saumur\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2441395606009212e-18, \"text\": \"Saumur\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saumur\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saumur\"}, {\"begin\": 1388, \"end\": 1398, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"score\": 0.9999481501095222, \"rank\": 3.103782187012972e-05, \"text\": \"equestrian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Equestrianism\"}, {\"begin\": 1399, \"end\": 1403, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gold_medal\", \"score\": 0.9893403786351527, \"rank\": 0.006802192644670563, \"text\": \"gold\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gold_medal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gold_medal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He then\\u00a0passed it on to a group of young athletes to carry it around the capital.\", \"from\": 1433, \"to\": 1514, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After its Bastille Day appearance, the torch relay will visit Notre Dame Cathedral, the historic Sorbonne University and the Louvre Museum.\", \"from\": 1516, \"to\": 1655, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1613, \"end\": 1632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sorbonne\", \"score\": 0.8098957963809117, \"rank\": 0.20935341108823657, \"text\": \"Sorbonne University\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sorbonne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sorbonne\"}, {\"begin\": 1641, \"end\": 1654, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Louvre Museum\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will then move on to other Paris landmarks on Monday.\", \"from\": 1656, \"to\": 1712, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1686, \"end\": 1691, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 2.8559624563145145e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This year's Bastille Day celebrations offer Macron a moment of distraction from the political turmoil he unleashed with asnap electionthat weakened his centrist party and his presidency.The result left the country with a deadlocked parliamentand no one clearly in charge.\", \"from\": 1714, \"to\": 1985, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1758, \"end\": 1764, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.117279595447976e-32, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The leftist alliance that won the most seats is struggling to agree on a candidate to replace Prime Minister Gabriel Attal, who could leave within days.\", \"from\": 1987, \"to\": 2139, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2096, \"end\": 2109, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gabriel Attal\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriel_Attal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is little sign of a ruling majority emerging from parliament, which is split into three loose camps.\", \"from\": 2140, \"to\": 2246, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Meanwhile, Macron is barred by the constitution from calling new elections for a period of 12 months.\", \"from\": 2247, \"to\": 2348, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2258, \"end\": 2264, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.117279595447976e-32, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As a result, the European Union's second-largest economy, a nuclear-armed G7 power and a permanent member of the UN Security Council, is rudderless.\", \"from\": 2350, \"to\": 2498, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2376, \"end\": 2381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999995587150871, \"rank\": 1.2598890305146585e-07, \"text\": \"Union\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2424, \"end\": 2426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_of_Seven\", \"score\": 0.9999968899395003, \"rank\": 3.1100701145540615e-06, \"text\": \"G7\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_of_Seven\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Group_of_Seven\"}, {\"begin\": 2463, \"end\": 2482, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations_Security_Council\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.2429333546084606e-12, \"text\": \"UN Security Council\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations_Security_Council\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Nations_Security_Council\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is a worrying situation for markets and for France's allies alike.\", \"from\": 2499, \"to\": 2570, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2548, \"end\": 2554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9989634872975586, \"rank\": 0.0010260130694498633, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On July 14, 1789, revolutionaries stormed the Bastille fortress and prison in Paris, marking the beginning of the French Revolution and the end of the monarchy.\", \"from\": 2572, \"to\": 2732, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2618, \"end\": 2626, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Storming_of_the_Bastille\", \"score\": 0.9999964138078852, \"rank\": 3.586091267637556e-06, \"text\": \"Bastille\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Storming_of_the_Bastille\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Storming_of_the_Bastille\"}, {\"begin\": 2650, \"end\": 2655, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 2.8559624563145145e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The holiday is central to the French calendar, with events held throughout the country.\", \"from\": 2734, \"to\": 2821, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2764, \"end\": 2770, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.505261373725146, \"rank\": 0.7963014140834302, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It aims to embody the national motto of \\\"liberty, equality and fraternity.\\\"\", \"from\": 2822, \"to\": 2897, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"dh/wd (AP, AFP)\", \"from\": 2899, \"to\": 2914, \"entities\": []}]}"